Ahmed Kathrada died on Tuesday at the age of 87 and an official funeral led by Deputy President Cyril Ramaphosa is being held at Westpark Cemetary. JOHANNESBURG - A memorial and funeral service for struggle stalwart Ahmed Kathrada is being held at the Westpark Cemetery in Johannesburg on Wednesday.Kathrada died on Tuesday at the age of 87.He is receiving an official funeral being led by Deputy President Cyril Ramaphosa.President Jacob Zuma says he will not be attending Ahmed Kathrada s memorial service and funeral in compliance with the wishes of the stalwart s family.Kathrada will be buried according to Muslim rites.